    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured person transported by helicopter to shore-based medical facility",
      "Physician evaluation and diagnosis of bicep tendon tear",
      "Incident reported to BSEE Lake Jackson District at 1050 hours",
      "BSEE inspectors conducted onsite investigation",
      "Post-incident investigation of BJSA and work procedures"
    ],
    "summary": "At 0955 hours on 2 October 2019, a Pipeline Technician sustained a bicep tendon tear while manually lifting a one-inch high pressure hose from a suspended 4'x4'x3' metal basket on the High Island A 474 A facility. The basket was suspended by crane approximately two to three feet off the deck and positioned half on another basket and half over the deck. The work area was congested with other baskets, bottle racks, and equipment. The injured person felt a 'pop' in his upper right arm while reaching over the top edge of the basket to retrieve items. The technician required surgical intervention.",
